    • Constructor Detail

      • Travel

        public Travel(java.util.UUID identifier,
              java.lang.String name,
              boolean isArrivalTime,
              Address startPoint,
              Address endPoint,
              java.util.Set<Route> routes,
              java.util.Set<TimeConstraint> timeConstraints)
       throws ValidationException
        create a new travel. A travel defines a start and endpoint and can have multiple routes that each define a concrete way to reach the endpoints departing from the starting point. Note that all routes of a travel share the same start and endpoint. To be useful travels should contain at least one route.
        Parameters:
        identifier - The UUID of the travel.
        name - The name given to this particular travel by the user. If a user decides to create a travel with the starting point his/her home address and the endpoint his/her work address it could be named "home-work".
        isArrivalTime - If true then the TimeIntervalConstraint represents the interval of arrival. ex. A user may want to reach the endpoint between 10:00 - 10:30. If false then the TimeIntervalConstraints represents the interval of departure. ex. A user may want to depart from the starting point between 20:00 and 20:20. Currently isArrivalTime is nowhere used.
        startPoint - The address that represents the departing location of the travel.
        endPoint - The address that represents the destination or endpoint of the travel.
        routes - The concrete ways the reach the endpoint departing from the starting point.
        timeConstraints - The set of time constraints created by a user. ex. a user can create a WeekDayConstraint [1,1,0,0,0,0,0] to indicate that he/she only makes this travel on monday and tuesday. Furthermore the user can add a TimeIntervalConstraint "20:00-21:00" indicating the approximate time of traveling. Notifications are only sent to a user if the timeConstraints are valid.
        Throws:
        ValidationException
